You: Are you okay?
The boy doesn't respond
Snap out of it
You: HEY, SNAP OUT OF IT
You slap the boy.
He looks up at you in shock...
Boy: WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?!?
Help him
You sit down next to the boy. He keeps hyperventilating and staring at the floor. There are tears in his eyes.
You: It is important for you to breathe, I can help you with that.
You: Just do as I do
The boy joins in.
You keep counting and breathing until you notice the boy has calmed down.
You: Is that better?
The boy nods slightly
"You should find some help"
You: You should probably seek help. Some people outside must know what to do.
The boy gives a nod
Boy: Thank you...
